WEBVTT

00:02.020 --> 00:04.340
- DCI Hicks, Elaine is joining us as
your new DI.

00:04.340 --> 00:06.100
- Is she working for you?
- Absolutely not.

00:06.100 --> 00:08.460
- You're the Renko that got stabbed,
right?

00:08.460 --> 00:10.460
- Hello, Daniel.
- Hello, Mum.

00:11.820 --> 00:14.580
- We have just been told to withdraw
the surveillance.

00:15.580 --> 00:17.540
- Jesus, what is on that flash
drive?

00:18.620 --> 00:21.580
- Yeah, but how long does it say
we've got?
- Five years.

00:21.580 --> 00:23.140
- I need to talk to my wife.

00:23.140 --> 00:24.580
- Charlie, is that you?

00:24.580 --> 00:25.860
- Who is this?

00:25.860 --> 00:27.380
- I think you know who we are.

00:28.740 --> 00:33.780
- Is it true?
- Yes. Which is why I'm asking you
to help me.

00:33.780 --> 00:35.340
- I need that flash drive.

00:35.340 --> 00:36.540
- No.

00:38.000 --> 00:44.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:57.500 --> 00:59.820
- He's gone back to the public call
box on Exeter Place.

00:59.820 --> 01:01.700
Unit Two, you're prime to intercept.

01:01.700 --> 01:03.900
[PHONE RINGS]

01:05.379 --> 01:07.300
Hicks' residence.

01:07.300 --> 01:08.820
- I haven't got it.

01:08.820 --> 01:11.420
- I'm sorry? Is that Charlie?

01:11.420 --> 01:15.620
Can you say that again? The line's
bad.

01:15.620 --> 01:17.020
- Renko took it. It's gone.

01:19.100 --> 01:20.420
- Well, Charlie.

01:20.420 --> 01:23.460
I don't know what to say.

01:23.460 --> 01:25.860
If that's the case...

01:25.860 --> 01:28.060
then I really can't help you.

01:29.860 --> 01:31.060
I'm sorry.

01:36.580 --> 01:38.100
[TYRES SQUEAL]

02:00.060 --> 02:01.220
[TASER BUZZES]

02:13.300 --> 02:15.420
- I'm looking for Will Benedetti on
news.

02:15.420 --> 02:17.380
- Oh, yeah, he's just over there.
- Thank you.

02:21.940 --> 02:22.980
Will Benedetti?

02:25.100 --> 02:26.780
DI Renko. We spoke.

02:28.060 --> 02:29.660
Can we talk somewhere private?

02:44.020 --> 02:45.420
- No...

03:00.340 --> 03:01.940
- Christ!

03:12.660 --> 03:14.420
I don't get it. Why come to me?

03:15.620 --> 03:18.220
- Your name's on the website. You
answered the phone.

03:19.620 --> 03:23.260
So you need to listen. Really listen
to what I'm saying.

03:23.260 --> 03:27.900
They're killing everyone who's seen
it. Everyone. Which means you.

03:28.900 --> 03:32.580
So if you want to protect yourself,
you need to run the story.

03:38.500 --> 03:41.660
- OK. OK, I can... I can do it. I can
do that.

03:41.660 --> 03:44.780
But I'm going to need the full
dossier, everything you've got.

03:44.780 --> 03:47.580
- I can't do that. I need to hold
something back.

03:47.580 --> 03:48.860
But I can give you enough.

04:12.620 --> 04:15.740
- I need to retrieve the Hard Sun
file.

04:15.740 --> 04:18.740
You have a copy on a flash drive.

04:18.740 --> 04:20.620
I need you to tell me where it is.

04:20.620 --> 04:23.100
- I already told them 100 times.

04:24.780 --> 04:28.020
Elaine... Renko took it.

04:28.020 --> 04:30.380
- Took it where?

04:31.780 --> 04:33.700
- My name is Elaine Renko.

04:33.700 --> 04:37.300
If you are watching this, I've been
murdered by the British state.

04:37.300 --> 04:40.020
During the course of a recent
investigation,

04:40.020 --> 04:43.420
my colleague DCI Charlie Hicks and I
came into contact with

04:43.420 --> 04:47.420
a classified government file,
code-named Hard Sun.

04:47.420 --> 04:50.140
- I know you love your family,
Charlie.

04:50.140 --> 04:52.820
So as a mother...

04:52.820 --> 04:55.300
and a daughter...

04:59.100 --> 05:01.500
...please don't make me do this.

05:08.260 --> 05:10.380
Where's Elaine Renko?

05:10.380 --> 05:12.660
- I don't know.

05:14.020 --> 05:15.460
- I see.

05:16.660 --> 05:18.460
- Come on, now. Just stop it. Turn
it off!

05:18.460 --> 05:20.620
- It's not like you're giving me any
choice, Charlie.

05:20.620 --> 05:24.780
If I don't get back that file, can
you imagine what will happen next?

05:24.780 --> 05:27.700
The anarchy? Come on!

05:29.220 --> 05:32.140
Why would you unleash that?

05:32.140 --> 05:33.260
Help me.

05:34.620 --> 05:36.100
Please...

05:37.620 --> 05:40.220
Help Simone and Hailey.

05:41.740 --> 05:44.580
And if not, then for God's sake you
help your baby.

05:45.740 --> 05:48.740
Tell me where to find Elaine!

05:53.060 --> 05:56.140
- I... can't!

05:58.020 --> 05:59.460
- Start with the wife.

06:06.580 --> 06:08.060
[PHONE RINGS]

06:09.220 --> 06:10.860
- Simone Hicks?

06:10.860 --> 06:14.340
- Mrs Hicks, this is Detective Chief
Superintendent Mark Donnellan.

06:14.340 --> 06:16.460
- What's wrong? Is Charlie OK?

06:16.460 --> 06:18.700
- You leave her alone.

06:18.700 --> 06:21.300
She... she's pregnant!

06:21.300 --> 06:23.740
- Not for long.

06:23.740 --> 06:25.060
- Simone Hicks?

06:25.060 --> 06:27.940
DS Angie Jones. You spoke to my
colleague.

06:27.940 --> 06:29.780
- What's going on?

06:29.780 --> 06:31.580
- Can you come with us, please?

06:31.580 --> 06:34.700
We need to talk about Charlie. It
won't take a moment.

06:40.620 --> 06:41.940
- What's going on?

06:41.940 --> 06:43.900
Is Charlie OK?

06:43.900 --> 06:46.900
- All right, that's-that's enough!
- Where's the flash drive?

06:46.900 --> 06:49.700
- I sent Elaine to a dead drop. Call
it off.

06:49.700 --> 06:52.500
- What dead drop?
- Call it off!
- Where?

06:52.500 --> 06:54.700
- A loose brick in an alley. Now
call it off!

06:54.700 --> 06:56.500
- What alley?

06:56.500 --> 07:00.620
- Behind the anarchist book shop in
Stroud Green! Now call it OFF!!!

07:00.620 --> 07:02.180
- You're lying, Charlie.

07:11.660 --> 07:13.140
- Where are we going?

07:14.460 --> 07:15.940
- YOU LEAVE HER ALONE!

07:15.940 --> 07:17.180
- TELL ME WHERE IT IS!

07:17.180 --> 07:19.300
- I DON'T KNOW WHERE IT IS!

07:19.300 --> 07:21.220
- Last chance!

07:21.220 --> 07:23.260
Simone's dead.

07:23.260 --> 07:27.860
You are watching her die! You are
killing your baby!

07:27.860 --> 07:30.700
[HE ROARS] Do it.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.940
- Be alert, we have an incoming Code
Yellow.

07:32.940 --> 07:35.900
- Stand down!
- Code yellow, incoming.
- Stand down!

07:39.740 --> 07:43.900
- In order to protect myself, DCI
Hicks and our loved ones...

07:43.900 --> 07:47.540
I've made a partial version of the
Hard Sun dossier available

07:47.540 --> 07:48.940
to a newspaper of record.

07:48.940 --> 07:51.300
- What newspaper? Trace it!
- I'm already on it.

07:51.300 --> 07:53.060
- The state will do its best to
suppress

07:53.060 --> 07:54.580
the release of this information.

07:54.580 --> 07:56.860
Anticipating this,

07:56.860 --> 08:00.660
a full copy of the Hard Sun dossier
will be kept with this statement.

08:00.660 --> 08:02.660
- The flash drive was accessed here.

08:03.900 --> 08:06.460
- This dossier contains a complete
record

08:06.460 --> 08:09.260
of the British State's Civil Defence
Emergency Planning

08:09.260 --> 08:11.340
related to the Hard Sun event...

08:11.340 --> 08:13.020
- This is a police raid.

08:13.020 --> 08:16.100
Do not touch your mobile phones, do
not touch your computers.

08:16.100 --> 08:18.580
- ...including plans for dissident
control,

08:18.580 --> 08:21.180
- the imposition of martial law...
- Where's Will Benedetti?

08:21.180 --> 08:23.860
- ...and provisions currently under
way for the establishment

08:23.860 --> 08:25.860
of internment camps.

08:25.860 --> 08:28.140
If any harm should come to me,

08:28.140 --> 08:31.660
to DCI Hicks or to any of our loved
ones,

08:31.660 --> 08:34.860
this statement and the complete Hard
Sun dossier will then be

08:34.860 --> 08:38.980
released to the media and the
internet and would be undeniable.

08:41.140 --> 08:44.580
Whatever you read, remember, I have
much more.

09:41.860 --> 09:43.060
- CAR HORN BLARES

10:39.500 --> 10:42.340
- This has been described as
"possibly the greatest hoax"

10:42.340 --> 10:46.380
"of its kind since the Hitler
Diaries."

10:46.380 --> 10:48.620
How do you feel about that?

10:49.780 --> 10:51.180
- Well, obviously not great.

10:52.380 --> 10:55.540
Look, the truth is I was offered
something too good to be true.

10:56.860 --> 11:00.260
But in the moment, I had to balance
urgency and time pressure

11:00.260 --> 11:03.660
against what I considered to be the
public's right to know.

11:05.540 --> 11:06.980
So I made a call.

11:06.980 --> 11:10.500
- And in retrospect, do you think
you made the right call?

11:11.700 --> 11:15.620
- Well, it was a call that cost me
my career and my reputation,

11:15.620 --> 11:18.580
if that answers your question?

11:18.580 --> 11:21.740
- Will Benedetti, thank you for
being on Hard Talk.

11:22.940 --> 11:28.420
Perhaps inevitably, despite or maybe
because of these disavowals,

11:28.420 --> 11:32.380
the Hard Sun hoax has given rise to
its own so-called

11:32.380 --> 11:34.100
"Truther" movement.

11:34.100 --> 11:37.260
On certain corners of the internet,
you can

11:37.260 --> 11:41.340
find as many conspiracy theories as
there are stars in the sky.

11:41.340 --> 11:46.460
Did the now discredited file refer
to a meteor? Or a comet?

11:46.460 --> 11:49.780
Or, perhaps a catastrophic solar
storm?

11:49.780 --> 11:51.620
- Daniel...
- Well, that's it...

11:51.620 --> 11:54.060
- You know it's after hours. Back to
bed, please.

11:54.060 --> 11:55.180
- Thanks for watching.

12:06.540 --> 12:09.540
- Every government agency is
preparing for the Hard Sun...

12:09.540 --> 12:11.740
Humanity's days on Earth are
numbered.

12:13.340 --> 12:15.980
We have 1,800 days,

12:15.980 --> 12:19.500
and our governments are spending
those days lying to us.

12:19.500 --> 12:24.740
The first question to ask is - would
the Government lie to you?

12:24.740 --> 12:27.340
And the answer is of course.

12:27.340 --> 12:29.660
As far as our governments are
concerned,

12:29.660 --> 12:32.380
this topic must remain above Top
Secret.

12:32.380 --> 12:36.500
Reality is broken, the truth must be
hidden.

12:36.500 --> 12:38.860
And the masses need a teaching

12:38.860 --> 12:41.260
proportional to their limited
knowledge.

12:41.260 --> 12:43.820
These fictions are necessary for the
people,

12:43.820 --> 12:46.980
and the truth becomes deadly to
those whom

12:46.980 --> 12:49.700
they believe are not strong enough
to contemplate it.

12:51.580 --> 12:54.940
- They're doing it, them in there.
MI5.

12:54.940 --> 12:58.820
They take the truth and fold it into
whatever shape they want.

12:58.820 --> 13:01.340
They turn a leak into a conspiracy
theory.

13:01.340 --> 13:02.980
It's like, I don't know, origami.

13:02.980 --> 13:04.620
- Nah, nah.

13:04.620 --> 13:07.260
They think they've got it all sealed
off, but they're wrong.

13:09.260 --> 13:12.220
It's out of the box, and you can't
put it back.

13:12.220 --> 13:13.660
[DOOR OPENS]

13:16.940 --> 13:19.820
- You see, the people who believe in
it,

13:19.820 --> 13:22.500
all the freaks and the nutters, the
religious fanatics

13:22.500 --> 13:24.260
and the psychos,

13:24.260 --> 13:26.620
they're all going to come crawling
out the woodwork.

13:29.140 --> 13:31.580
[SHE SCREAMS]

13:34.980 --> 13:37.340
- You know, it just makes my head
hurt.

13:37.340 --> 13:41.060
You know, I feel like I've got to
just cram it all in.

13:41.060 --> 13:44.540
It's just like I'm forcing myself to
remember everything, you know,

13:44.540 --> 13:46.500
every detail.

13:47.620 --> 13:49.860
Cos I know that soon, it's going to
be gone.

13:49.860 --> 13:52.340
I mean, all you want to do is
protect the people that you love.

13:52.340 --> 13:54.900
So how are you supposed to deal with
it, knowing that you can't?

13:54.900 --> 13:57.620
All right, knowing that no-one can?
Ever.

14:00.380 --> 14:02.100
Five years.

14:03.740 --> 14:05.500
What's the point?

14:05.500 --> 14:10.620
- What's the point? The point is -
everything you love is here now.

14:14.020 --> 14:15.860
That is all that matters.

14:19.300 --> 14:22.220
- The funny thing is, is that
there's only one person that

14:22.220 --> 14:24.700
I can talk to about this on this
entire planet.

14:24.700 --> 14:27.140
And that's you.

14:27.140 --> 14:31.660
I mean, I am lying to everyone on
this Earth...

14:33.820 --> 14:35.460
...but you...

14:49.180 --> 14:51.500
[KNOCKING]

15:09.900 --> 15:11.500
- You shouldn't come here.

15:11.500 --> 15:12.820
- It's not being watched.

15:12.820 --> 15:14.860
- That you know of.

15:16.620 --> 15:18.740
- Did he tell you his wife left him?

15:20.220 --> 15:21.420
- No.

15:21.420 --> 15:23.420
- Of course he didn't. No.

15:24.660 --> 15:26.940
So what is taking so long?

15:26.940 --> 15:31.780
- Lack of evidence. There's nothing
to suggest that Hicks killed Butler.

15:31.780 --> 15:34.340
- He's sleeping with the man's wife.
- That's motive, not evidence.

15:34.340 --> 15:36.220
- Then find some evidence.

15:36.220 --> 15:37.980
- Honestly, what does it matter?

15:37.980 --> 15:40.380
In your head, you've already
convicted him.

15:40.380 --> 15:42.420
- It matters because we cut you a
deal!

15:43.500 --> 15:46.860
We keep your son out of prison, you
bring us Charlie Hicks.

15:48.300 --> 15:49.780
Are we clear?

16:11.660 --> 16:14.940
[PHONE RINGS]

16:19.060 --> 16:21.340
- Sorry, Dad. It's Charlie.

16:21.340 --> 16:24.060
Erm... you carry on watching.

16:31.260 --> 16:34.740
- Hey. It's really late.
- Oh, I know, I'm...

16:34.740 --> 16:37.980
I'm sorry. I got caught up with
something.

16:37.980 --> 16:39.860
How's Hailey?

16:39.860 --> 16:41.780
- Yeah, she's great.

16:41.780 --> 16:44.540
Oh, she did have another Barney with
Rochelle, though.

16:44.540 --> 16:46.300
- Oh? What about?

16:46.300 --> 16:47.980
- Whether God has a willy?

16:47.980 --> 16:50.940
Apparently, he doesn't because he's
not a boy.

16:50.940 --> 16:52.580
- That's good to know.

16:54.340 --> 16:57.420
How are you? Hm? How's the bump?

16:58.460 --> 17:01.540
- She's kicking right now, actually.
- Yeah?

17:02.820 --> 17:05.700
Well, you know why that is, don't
you?

17:05.700 --> 17:07.020
She wants to come home.

17:07.020 --> 17:09.740
- We'll come home when you tell me
what's going on.

17:09.740 --> 17:12.099
- Hey. Nothing's going on!
- So who were those people?

17:12.099 --> 17:15.500
- Look, I told you. They were...
They were coppers, all right?

17:15.500 --> 17:18.540
They were police. Look, how many
times?

17:18.540 --> 17:21.980
Look, there was a threat to my life,
and for about five minutes,

17:21.980 --> 17:24.819
it seemed credible. But it was
nothing.

17:24.819 --> 17:27.660
Look, Simone, I don't know what else
to say.

17:27.660 --> 17:29.460
Huh? The kids are safe.

17:30.980 --> 17:34.980
And you're safe. And we're all safe.

17:42.340 --> 17:45.620
- Look, erm... I've got to go.

17:48.380 --> 17:51.060
Hailey's going to call you tomorrow.

17:51.060 --> 17:54.220
She wants to talk to you about her
project. It's about spiders.

17:56.700 --> 17:58.540
- Yeah, yeah, OK.

18:00.820 --> 18:03.980
Listen, erm, give my love to your
mum and dad, yeah?

18:03.980 --> 18:06.220
- Good night, Charlie.

18:08.620 --> 18:10.660
- Go and kiss Hailey for me.

18:10.660 --> 18:14.060
And the bump. Give the bump a kiss.

18:15.300 --> 18:16.860
- The bump says good night.

18:17.860 --> 18:19.660
- All right, good night.

18:37.180 --> 18:38.620
[KNOCKING]

18:46.580 --> 18:49.540
- Charlie, it's late.

19:53.100 --> 19:55.060
[BUZZ]

20:06.020 --> 20:07.540
- Hello, mate.

20:08.660 --> 20:10.180
What are you doing up?

20:11.500 --> 20:13.620
- Erm, er, rowing practice.

20:13.620 --> 20:15.380
- Rowing?
- Yeah.

20:15.380 --> 20:16.900
- Oh, since when?

20:16.900 --> 20:18.860
- Since, like, a term or something?

20:18.860 --> 20:22.380
- Oh! You, er, you had a proper
breakfast?

20:22.380 --> 20:24.220
- Not yet.

20:26.100 --> 20:28.820
- Right, how about I do you some
eggs and then I give you a lift?

20:28.820 --> 20:30.900
- How's that?
- Yeah. Yeah...

20:32.100 --> 20:34.020
- All right, good man, come on.

20:42.380 --> 20:44.540
- Morning.
- Morning.

20:47.500 --> 20:49.260
- You all right, boss?

20:49.260 --> 20:51.340
- Sorry. Bit of a scare with the
baby.

20:51.340 --> 20:52.980
- No! Everything all right?

20:52.980 --> 20:55.140
- Yeah, false alarm. Braxton Hicks.

20:55.140 --> 20:57.580
- Ah.
- It's a bit early for that, innit?

20:57.580 --> 20:59.820
- No, they can come at six weeks,
Braxton Hicks.

20:59.820 --> 21:02.540
- Says Keith, father of hundreds.
- Six.

21:02.540 --> 21:04.660
- Six?!
- Yeah, we live in a shoe.

21:05.860 --> 21:07.300
Simone all right, though?

21:07.300 --> 21:10.020
- She's fine, mate. You know how it
is.

21:10.020 --> 21:12.220
Right, let's, er, let's do this.
What we got?

21:24.820 --> 21:28.020
- Dominic Vaughan and Sabina
Kesinovic, husband and wife

21:28.020 --> 21:30.860
- and business partners.
- Yeah? What kind of business?

21:30.860 --> 21:33.420
- Sunstride PR. Corporate Public
Relations.

21:33.420 --> 21:35.980
- Reputation management.
- What, we got a list of clients?

21:35.980 --> 21:38.100
- George and Herbie are looking into
it.

21:38.100 --> 21:41.140
- Is there any interest groups their
work might have offended? Political?

21:41.140 --> 21:44.780
Environmental?
- Checking that, too.
- Any kids? Family?

21:44.780 --> 21:48.500
- No kids. Workaholics. He's got no
family to speak of.

21:48.500 --> 21:50.660
- Hers live in Denmark.

21:50.660 --> 21:53.020
We're notifying them via the
Roskilde police.

21:54.420 --> 21:57.620
- Right, let's walk it through. What
we saying?

21:57.620 --> 21:59.580
He came in from what, the back door?

21:59.580 --> 22:02.300
- Using an electric pick-lock -
professional locksmith tool.

22:02.300 --> 22:04.860
- Traceable?
- Nah. You can get 'em anywhere.

22:04.860 --> 22:07.660
- Mr Vaughan tries to protect his
wife. Our boy beats him down.

22:07.660 --> 22:09.380
He breaks Mr Vaughan's arms and
legs...

22:09.380 --> 22:11.340
- And makes him, y'know...

22:11.340 --> 22:12.820
- Watch.

22:16.180 --> 22:17.620
- So, what are we thinking?

22:20.100 --> 22:22.980
- He's lost some traditional male
status role -

22:22.980 --> 22:25.220
husband, father, provider.

22:25.220 --> 22:28.620
So, he's looking to re-assert his
identity as a man,

22:28.620 --> 22:31.940
to be physically and sexually
dominant.

22:31.940 --> 22:34.060
- All right...

22:34.060 --> 22:36.020
so he's a dick.

22:38.060 --> 22:39.780
Right, this was planned,

22:39.780 --> 22:43.260
he knew the house, he probably knew
the victims.

22:43.260 --> 22:45.940
And it seems like their lives
revolved around their work,

22:45.940 --> 22:47.940
so... well, let's start there.

23:04.940 --> 23:06.820
- Happy birthday!

23:06.820 --> 23:09.580
- Oh! Wow!

23:11.660 --> 23:16.740
- Thank you.
- I didn't buy it. I made it.

23:16.740 --> 23:19.340
- Oh! You did not make this?!

23:19.340 --> 23:21.260
No way!

23:21.260 --> 23:23.380
- Can you read what it says?

23:24.620 --> 23:27.900
- Well, why don't you read it to
Mummy, hey?

23:28.980 --> 23:33.660
- My mummy is kind. My mummy drives
a car.

23:33.660 --> 23:36.100
My mummy...
[DOORBELL RINGS]

23:36.100 --> 23:38.780
Your mummy needs to answer the door.

23:46.300 --> 23:48.020
Chris?

23:48.020 --> 23:49.500
What's up?

23:50.460 --> 23:54.220
- Nothing. I just, erm, popped by to
give you this.

23:54.220 --> 23:57.140
It's just a birthday card, but many
happy returns.

24:00.020 --> 24:01.820
Life begins and all that.

24:01.820 --> 24:03.980
So where are the kids?

24:03.980 --> 24:07.500
- They're upstairs, getting ready
for school.
- Oh, fair enough.

24:08.740 --> 24:10.740
Well, give them a kiss from me.

24:10.740 --> 24:12.700
Tell them I'll see them soon.

24:16.980 --> 24:19.140
Have you been watching the news?

24:19.140 --> 24:20.700
- What news?

24:20.700 --> 24:22.940
- The Hard Sun.

24:22.940 --> 24:24.380
- Chris, honestly.

24:24.380 --> 24:26.820
Is this the thing that you keep
sending me the links about?

24:26.820 --> 24:29.220
I haven't got time!

24:29.220 --> 24:31.300
What is it?

24:32.620 --> 24:34.340
- Nothing.

24:38.140 --> 24:39.620
It doesn't matter.

24:42.100 --> 24:43.820
Happy birthday.

24:47.100 --> 24:48.860
See you in a bit.

25:16.460 --> 25:19.180
- Oops. Sorry. I was miles away!

25:19.180 --> 25:21.500
- No worries. Wait. Is it Mari?

25:21.500 --> 25:22.740
- It is, yeah.

25:22.740 --> 25:24.620
- My god! How are you?

25:24.620 --> 25:27.500
- Um... I'm great! Thanks.

25:27.500 --> 25:29.340
- Books for your course?

25:29.340 --> 25:32.020
- Er, yeah. Er, essay on Milgram.

25:32.020 --> 25:33.420
- "Obedience To Authority."

25:34.660 --> 25:37.220
Listen, I was so sorry to hear about Alex.

25:40.140 --> 25:41.660
- That's very kind.

25:41.660 --> 25:43.620
- How are you bearing up?

25:43.620 --> 25:46.460
- Yeah. Good, really.

25:46.460 --> 25:47.740
Thank you.

25:47.740 --> 25:50.860
- Well... it was nice bumping into
you.

25:50.860 --> 25:52.860
- Yeah, you, too.

25:55.380 --> 25:57.820
- Are you still friends with Charlie
Hicks?

25:59.420 --> 26:02.100
- I see him every now and again,
yeah.

26:02.100 --> 26:04.900
- I wonder, could you give him a
message from me?

26:12.580 --> 26:15.780
- She said she knew me. I've never
seen her before.

26:15.780 --> 26:17.820
- Who was she? Did you get her name?

26:17.820 --> 26:21.780
- Well, I don't know who she was!
- Well, what did she say?

26:21.780 --> 26:23.980
- She gave me a message for you.

26:25.180 --> 26:26.900
- What message?

26:28.220 --> 26:30.820
- She said, "Renko knows what you
did to Alex Butler."

26:30.820 --> 26:32.420
"And why."

26:41.980 --> 26:43.380
Charlie?

26:43.380 --> 26:44.460
Charlie?!

26:44.460 --> 26:45.940
- Yeah. Yeah, no, I'm here. Sorry.

26:45.940 --> 26:48.140
Listen, I'm just on my way to a
thing at the moment.

26:48.140 --> 26:51.100
- Can I call you back in a bit?
- Well, who was she?

26:51.100 --> 26:54.140
- I don't know. But I'm sure it's
nothing.

26:54.140 --> 26:57.180
I'll call you back when I can, OK?
Bye.

27:03.460 --> 27:05.260
- Problem?

27:05.260 --> 27:08.420
- Yeah. Yeah, it's just Simone, my
wife.

27:09.620 --> 27:11.620
I think she knows something's wrong.

27:12.740 --> 27:14.660
What am I supposed to tell her?

27:15.780 --> 27:18.380
- That's easy. Tell her a lie.

27:20.300 --> 27:24.340
- Yeah, well, I don't want to lie to
her. I love her.

28:05.300 --> 28:07.140
[PHONE RINGS]

28:14.740 --> 28:18.300
Hello. Your call cannot be taken at
the moment,

28:18.300 --> 28:21.220
so please leave your message after
the tone.

28:28.980 --> 28:31.900
- Sorry for the delay. I was on a
call.

28:31.900 --> 28:35.380
- DI Renko... DCI Hicks. And you
are?

28:35.380 --> 28:38.500
- Maggie Sweeting. Group Account
Director.

28:38.500 --> 28:40.980
Is there a problem? Are we in
trouble?

28:43.820 --> 28:48.500
Both of them? How? Was there a fire,
or...

28:48.500 --> 28:50.340
- I'm sure this must come as a
shock.

28:50.340 --> 28:53.700
- An accident?
- But we do need to ask some
questions.

28:53.700 --> 28:55.580
- Absolutely. Yeah, of course.

28:55.580 --> 28:59.260
Erm... except, I feel a bit, erm, I
ju... I need to, erm,

28:59.260 --> 29:02.780
splash my face, if that's OK, some
cold water to...?

29:02.780 --> 29:03.940
- Of course.

29:21.220 --> 29:23.540
- Can you believe our Maggie's 40?!

29:23.540 --> 29:26.300
- I don't want to! What age does
that make me?

29:26.300 --> 29:27.380
- Anyone?

29:27.380 --> 29:29.860
- Oh, cheers, babe. It's a bit early
for me, love.

29:29.860 --> 29:31.260
Why don't I put the kettle on?

29:31.260 --> 29:33.540
[DOORBELL RINGS]

29:33.540 --> 29:36.020
- Cake!

29:36.020 --> 29:39.260
- What time are we picking up the
kids, Geoff?
- I'd better go now.

29:41.740 --> 29:42.940
Chris?

29:46.860 --> 29:49.100
No! No, no!

29:51.020 --> 29:53.620
- Sit down! Sit on your arse!

29:55.660 --> 29:57.220
[PHONE BUZZES]

30:03.060 --> 30:04.580
Oh, God!

30:05.780 --> 30:07.500
[THEY WHIMPER]

30:07.500 --> 30:09.660
Oh, my god! Chris!

30:11.340 --> 30:14.900
Oh, my god, Chris, don't hurt them,
please! Don't hurt them, please!

30:14.900 --> 30:17.420
- Say a word to the police, one
word, I end them all.

30:17.420 --> 30:20.740
Do you believe me?
- Yes! Yes, I do! Yes, I do, I
believe you!

30:20.740 --> 30:22.700
Oh, my god, please, yes, I believe
you.

30:22.700 --> 30:24.860
- Cos we both know that you lie,
don't we?

30:26.540 --> 30:30.580
Have you heard about Dominic, by the
way?
- Oh, Chris, no!

30:31.700 --> 30:33.620
- I made him feel what it was like.

30:35.060 --> 30:36.500
Crying like a baby, he was,

30:36.500 --> 30:38.180
begging me to stop,

30:38.180 --> 30:39.780
while I had his wife.

30:42.020 --> 30:45.260
Funny enough, that was the first
time I was ever unfaithful to you.

30:47.140 --> 30:49.100
You've got half an hour to get here.

30:49.100 --> 30:51.740
- I can't... I can't do that! I
can't!

30:51.740 --> 30:53.340
Don't make me do that!

30:54.700 --> 30:56.420
[PHONE BEEPS OFF]

31:02.140 --> 31:05.180
- It's maybe not all puppies and
rainbows between the victims.

31:05.180 --> 31:06.460
They joint-own the company,

31:06.460 --> 31:09.140
so they're pretty cagey about the
personal side of things,

31:09.140 --> 31:11.900
but it turns out Sabina was
consulting a divorce lawyer.

31:11.900 --> 31:13.460
- On what grounds?

31:13.460 --> 31:14.900
- The usual.

31:14.900 --> 31:16.660
- So who's the husband getting busy
with?

31:16.660 --> 31:18.460
- A colleague called Maggie
Sweeting.

31:28.420 --> 31:30.660
- So I had a gander at Maggie
Sweeting's inbox

31:30.660 --> 31:32.980
- and it turns out the husband...
- Ex-husband.

31:32.980 --> 31:35.060
- Well, estranged husband, is,

31:35.060 --> 31:37.220
I wouldn't exactly say howling at
the moon...

31:37.220 --> 31:39.540
- He sent her a dozen emails a day,
mostly web links.

31:39.540 --> 31:41.980
- Web links to what?
- Hard Sun.

31:43.180 --> 31:45.700
- It was a hoax they pulled on the
news a few weeks ago -

31:45.700 --> 31:49.060
a conspiracy to cover up the end of
the world as we know it and all that

31:49.060 --> 31:51.380
but he seemed a bit woo-woo for it.

31:52.460 --> 31:55.020
- All right. So, we need to know
more about the husband.

31:56.300 --> 31:59.140
- Does anyone here know where Maggie
Sweeting's gone?

32:16.700 --> 32:17.980
[PHONE BUZZES]

32:49.300 --> 32:50.980
[SHE WHIMPERS]

32:50.980 --> 32:52.060
Oh, no.

32:52.060 --> 32:53.980
Oh, no, no, no.

32:55.860 --> 32:57.260
[PHONE BUZZES]

32:58.580 --> 33:04.060
- Surprise! Happy birthday, Mum!

33:04.060 --> 33:06.100
- Happy birthday, Mum!

33:06.100 --> 33:09.220
- Happy birthday!

33:09.220 --> 33:10.740
[PHONE RINGS]

33:10.740 --> 33:11.940
[SHE WHIMPERS]

33:13.060 --> 33:14.820
- Happy birthday.

33:14.820 --> 33:17.580
- Where are they? Where are the
kids?!

33:17.580 --> 33:20.460
Where have you taken them? Where are
they?

33:21.820 --> 33:22.900
- They're playing.

33:23.940 --> 33:25.460
- Don't hurt them.

33:25.460 --> 33:26.780
Don't, please.

33:26.780 --> 33:29.100
Oh, God, please, Chris! Please don't
hurt them!

33:30.100 --> 33:31.460
- Not going to hurt them.

33:34.340 --> 33:35.700
I could never hurt them.

33:39.100 --> 33:40.380
They're what I live for.

33:40.380 --> 33:41.700
[CHILDREN PLAY]

33:43.100 --> 33:45.820
- But there is no future, so...

33:47.020 --> 33:49.380
...I'm just going to help make them
sleep.

33:49.380 --> 33:51.260
- Oh, no, don't say that! No,
please!

33:51.260 --> 33:54.140
Please don't, don't say that! Don't
do that, don't!

33:54.140 --> 33:56.220
- I can't let them suffer through
this.

33:59.580 --> 34:03.660
No mum, no dad. I can't.

34:03.660 --> 34:06.060
- Oh, God. Chris! Chris! Please!

34:06.060 --> 34:09.300
- Well, there's no point in you
crying now - you did this to us.

34:09.300 --> 34:10.980
You ended our family!

34:15.580 --> 34:17.659
Threw it all away.

34:21.179 --> 34:22.820
You got what you wanted.

34:25.100 --> 34:26.980
I hope you're happy.

34:26.980 --> 34:28.380
- Chris! Chris, please!

34:28.380 --> 34:31.500
What can I do? What? What? What can
I do? Please, please!

34:31.500 --> 34:34.020
I'm begging you. I am begging you,
please, please!

34:34.020 --> 34:35.340
What can I do?

34:42.780 --> 34:45.100
- You remember the place where we
made Jessica?

34:47.460 --> 34:49.020
[PHONE RINGS]

35:42.980 --> 35:44.060
- So what've we got?

35:45.500 --> 35:49.540
- I think we're safe to confirm an
interest in the Hard Sun thing.

35:49.540 --> 35:51.420
- Yeah? How much of an interest?

35:51.420 --> 35:56.020
- Erm, well, he's definitely a fan.

35:58.260 --> 36:01.300
- The husband's Chris Chapel,
self-employed joiner.

36:01.300 --> 36:03.580
Company went bust in 2012.

36:03.580 --> 36:07.660
He and Maggie separated last year
and he's taken the kids.

36:07.660 --> 36:10.220
- Look, we both know how this goes.

36:10.220 --> 36:13.980
What, we trace his phone signal,
deploy armed response

36:13.980 --> 36:15.420
and a hostage negotiator?

36:15.420 --> 36:17.300
Yeah, but that won't work.

36:17.300 --> 36:21.060
I've seen it before - he kills his
kids, he kills his wife.

36:21.060 --> 36:24.420
And then he kills himself cos that's
what they do, men like him.

36:24.420 --> 36:27.260
They kill the people that they love
because they're scared

36:27.260 --> 36:28.420
they can't protect them.

36:28.420 --> 36:29.500
- Boss...

36:29.500 --> 36:31.220
- I can't set that process in motion

36:31.220 --> 36:33.620
knowing that it ends with two dead
children.

36:33.620 --> 36:35.460
I can't do that.

36:35.460 --> 36:36.940
- All right, so?

36:36.940 --> 36:38.180
- So...

36:39.460 --> 36:42.540
...I've got Keith, tracking her
mobile.

36:42.540 --> 36:45.060
She's heading out of London - out to
the sticks.

36:46.500 --> 36:52.020
- I don't follow.
- Look, I'm saying that we do this - me and you.

36:52.020 --> 36:55.100
- Alone?
- Yeah.
- What, with no backup?

36:55.100 --> 36:56.820
- We haven't got time for that.

36:56.820 --> 36:59.060
Now, it's either me and you or it's
everyone,

36:59.060 --> 37:00.380
and if it's everyone,

37:00.380 --> 37:04.100
we might as well kill those kids
ourselves.

37:04.100 --> 37:06.300
Elaine, trust me.

37:37.220 --> 37:38.780
- Where are we going?

37:40.060 --> 37:41.300
- Nowhere nice.

37:47.340 --> 37:48.820
[PHONE RINGS]

37:54.980 --> 37:56.660
- Are you going to take that?

37:56.660 --> 37:57.780
- No.

37:59.180 --> 38:00.900
It's not important.

38:00.900 --> 38:04.020
- Hello, your call cannot be taken
at the moment,

38:04.020 --> 38:06.700
so please leave your message after
the tone.

38:06.700 --> 38:07.740
[TONE BEEPS]

38:36.460 --> 38:38.540
- OK, we're getting close.

38:41.540 --> 38:42.900
- Stop!

38:42.900 --> 38:44.340
Back up!

39:39.380 --> 39:41.500
[SHE WHIMPERS]

39:53.540 --> 39:55.740
- Where is he? Where's Chris?

39:55.740 --> 39:58.620
Do you want your kids to live? Adam
and Jessica?

39:58.620 --> 40:00.340
Then where is he?

40:00.340 --> 40:03.940
- We've come here to help you,
Maggie, but we don't have much time.

41:01.900 --> 41:03.140
[PHONE BUZZES]

41:10.580 --> 41:12.060
[RINGING TONE]

41:15.460 --> 41:16.580
[PHONE BUZZES]

41:19.020 --> 41:20.220
- Where are you?

41:21.580 --> 41:22.820
- Outside.

41:29.820 --> 41:30.980
I'm out the front.

41:55.340 --> 41:56.660
- Come here.

41:59.180 --> 42:00.500
Now.

42:07.140 --> 42:08.540
- Can I just say something?

42:09.900 --> 42:11.420
I need to say it for me.

42:11.420 --> 42:12.860
Please just let me say it.

42:15.500 --> 42:16.740
I am...

42:16.740 --> 42:19.140
I'm so sorry, Chris, I...

42:19.140 --> 42:20.980
...and I know what I did to you.

42:23.060 --> 42:24.660
I'm tru... I'm truly sorry.

42:25.820 --> 42:28.340
You... you deserve better.

42:32.220 --> 42:33.340
[SLIGHT BANG]

42:36.740 --> 42:39.020
Chris! Chris!

42:39.020 --> 42:42.500
Chris, what do I do? Please!

42:42.500 --> 42:45.780
Please, tell me what to do.

42:45.780 --> 42:47.420
- Come here!

42:55.740 --> 42:57.300
- WHISPERS:
- Oh, no.

43:05.220 --> 43:06.780
- On your knees!

43:10.220 --> 43:12.260
- Oh, it's OK. They're asleep.

43:12.260 --> 43:13.700
They're drugged.

43:43.980 --> 43:45.700
- Shush!
- Daddy!

43:47.340 --> 43:49.540
- We're police.
- Daddy!

43:49.540 --> 43:50.580
Daddy!

43:50.580 --> 43:51.660
- Aggh!

43:51.660 --> 43:53.700
- Help!

43:53.700 --> 43:55.780
- Look at you, you prick!

43:55.780 --> 43:58.500
You sad, sad wanker!

44:02.260 --> 44:03.300
[GUNSHOT]

44:08.860 --> 44:10.660
- Take the kids, circle back to the
car

44:10.660 --> 44:12.980
but don't call it in until you're
safe.

44:12.980 --> 44:14.340
Just do it.

44:17.780 --> 44:18.980
- Come on.

44:21.180 --> 44:24.060
- Adam! Jessica!

44:24.060 --> 44:26.420
- Are we lost?
- No. Shush!
- Where are you?

44:26.420 --> 44:28.380
- You need to be quiet now, really,
really quiet.

44:28.380 --> 44:31.300
- You tell me where you are! Right
now!

44:33.300 --> 44:37.980
Right now!
- I want to go home.
- It's OK.
- I want my mummy.

44:37.980 --> 44:40.780
- Adam, do you want to make me
angry?
- It's all right, shush.

44:40.780 --> 44:43.820
- Cos you're going to be in so much
trouble, you and your sister!

44:43.820 --> 44:45.380
- I want my mummy.

44:48.940 --> 44:50.300
- Adam?
- Shush!

44:52.900 --> 44:55.700
- WHISPERS:
- OK, Jessica, you stay here. Hide
here, OK?

44:55.700 --> 44:58.540
I want you to be quiet, really,
really quiet.

44:58.540 --> 45:00.140
Don't make a sound, don't move.

45:40.340 --> 45:41.380
[CHRIS GROANS]

46:03.340 --> 46:05.300
- Daddy!

46:05.300 --> 46:08.140
- Adam! Don't watch this! Don't
watch!

46:08.140 --> 46:10.060
Run away! Run away now!

46:10.060 --> 46:13.100
- Adam, stay where you are!
- Don't, Adam. Daddy's sick.

46:13.100 --> 46:15.820
You go find Mummy, find Mummy, OK?

46:16.940 --> 46:18.220
- Adam!

46:23.260 --> 46:24.740
[GUN CLICKS]

46:25.780 --> 46:27.180
- Adam!

46:28.780 --> 46:30.580
You stay where you are!

46:31.700 --> 46:36.100
Stay right there! I'm almost done
here.

46:39.140 --> 46:41.500
Don't make me come looking for you!

46:53.740 --> 46:55.220
- Oi!

46:55.220 --> 46:56.420
Bell end!

47:08.700 --> 47:10.180
- You're killing him!

47:13.940 --> 47:16.820
Charlie, his kid's watching, his
kid's watching!

47:22.900 --> 47:24.340
[CHRIS COUGHS]

47:50.540 --> 47:52.380
- Mummy!
- Jessica!

47:53.420 --> 47:55.020
Oh, Jessica!

47:57.860 --> 47:59.340
[SHE KISSES THEM]

48:00.620 --> 48:02.220
- You were right.

48:02.220 --> 48:05.900
There'll be more like this when the
news gets out - The Hard Sun thing.

48:07.820 --> 48:09.140
- Yeah.

48:11.620 --> 48:15.100
- You should talk to Simone. Tell
her the truth.

48:17.460 --> 48:19.060
- Yeah? And what's that?

48:19.060 --> 48:21.460
- I don't know. Make something up.

48:21.460 --> 48:23.020
Just talk to her.

48:39.100 --> 48:42.940
- Charlie! What are you doing here?
What's happened?

48:42.940 --> 48:44.460
- I've been in the country.

48:45.540 --> 48:46.900
I hate the country.

48:46.900 --> 48:48.540
It smells and things live in it.

48:51.300 --> 48:54.420
Look, I just want to say one thing,
all right?

48:54.420 --> 48:57.100
And then I'm going to go home, I'm
going to have a shower

48:57.100 --> 48:58.780
and play on the Xbox.

49:00.300 --> 49:02.220
Yeah, I bought an Xbox, by the way.

49:02.220 --> 49:03.700
- OK.

49:04.860 --> 49:07.020
- Listen, what I've got to say, all
right,

49:07.020 --> 49:08.700
I'm not trying to be a caveman.

49:08.700 --> 49:10.140
It's not a man and woman thing.

49:12.300 --> 49:13.700
It's a love thing.

49:15.620 --> 49:16.940
Does that make sense?

49:18.500 --> 49:19.900
Simone, look at me.

49:20.900 --> 49:26.060
You are safe, because I will protect
you, no matter what.

49:27.340 --> 49:30.820
You, Hailey, and the bump.

49:32.740 --> 49:38.900
And as long as I draw breath, no-one
will hurt you ever...

49:40.060 --> 49:44.020
...and if they try... well, I'll kill
them.

49:46.820 --> 49:48.940
I need you to understand that.

49:52.740 --> 49:53.780
- OK.

49:55.300 --> 49:57.380
- So, when do I get to bring you
home?

49:59.180 --> 50:01.060
How about tomorrow morning...

50:02.460 --> 50:03.700
...please?

50:08.500 --> 50:10.660
- Tomorrow sounds good.

50:24.460 --> 50:25.780
[PHONE RINGS]

50:41.100 --> 50:42.500
- Boss?

50:42.500 --> 50:43.860
- Evening, Renko.

50:45.060 --> 50:46.620
- What do you want?

50:46.620 --> 50:47.980
- To make your life easier.

50:49.060 --> 50:50.460
- What's that supposed to mean?

50:50.460 --> 50:53.060
- You wanted evidence. I'm sending
it through now.

50:59.340 --> 51:00.380
[PHONE BUZZES]

51:04.380 --> 51:05.620
- Shit.

51:12.100 --> 51:13.620
My god!

51:16.460 --> 51:17.860
You've got him.

51:23.420 --> 51:25.620
- Mum, it's all it is,

51:25.620 --> 51:28.700
I saw this thing on the news,

51:28.700 --> 51:31.220
this... this thing about the sun.

51:31.220 --> 51:33.620
And then, the next day or whatever,

51:33.620 --> 51:37.700
people all over the TV were saying
it was like a mistake or whatever.

51:42.460 --> 51:45.540
And that makes sense, because...

51:50.340 --> 51:54.300
...I've got this thing, in my head.

51:56.420 --> 51:59.420
I look at their eyes when they say
it's not true...

52:02.060 --> 52:03.940
...and I think they're lying.

52:05.940 --> 52:09.460
I've been thinking about it a lot,
actually.

52:09.460 --> 52:12.540
It's kind of been keeping me awake.

52:13.660 --> 52:18.220
It's just like, why would they
lie...

52:20.300 --> 52:21.700
...you know?

